Introduction

FlyWithMe, also known as the initialism FWM, was a South Korean girl group under FA Entertainment. Originally formed as a hip-hop dance group in 2008, they debuted as a girl group on June 27, 2018, with the release of their first digital single, "Your Face".

Shasa, Hai, and JeJe are the original members of the group, and had been part of the group since 2008. After the departure of member Jeje, Liae and Rea were added to the group in 2016. Later in 2018 Babi, Chure, Ati, Juya, Way, and Ella were added as well. However, multiple members left the group within the following years, with Way leaving in 2019, Liae, Ati, Juya, and Ella in 2020, and Rea, Babi, and Chure leaving in 2021.

Daya and Eve, previously members of Black Bunny, joined the group in 2021 after the disbandment of Black Bunny. Sometime between 2021 and 2022, Lena joined the group, followed by Garin and Ellie who joined in 2022. In 2023 Yuki joined the group with Garin leaving the group soon after.

Their first big performance was in collaboration with YG Entertainment at Tokyo Dome on June 13, 2018. They won the ''Minister of Health and Welfare Award'' in 2018.
